  <h2>How do you verify a PAGCOR license yourself?</h2>

  <p>Verification is not difficult, but it requires knowing where to look and what legitimate credentials look like. There are three reliable methods, and you should use at least two of them before trusting any platform with your money.</p>

  <h3>Method 1: The PAGCOR official registry</h3>

  <p>PAGCOR maintains a public registry of licensed operators on its official website at <strong>pagcor.ph</strong>. Navigate to the "Licensees" or "Regulatory" section and search for the operator by company name or brand name. The registry is updated quarterly and lists both e-Games and PIGO licensees with their license numbers, authorized game types, and license validity dates.</p>

  <p>Caveat: The PAGCOR website is not always easy to navigate, and the registry format has changed several times. If you cannot find an operator in the online registry, this does not automatically mean they are unlicensed &mdash; but it should raise a question that deserves a definitive answer before you deposit money.</p>

  <h3>Method 2: License number format verification</h3>

  <p>Legitimate PAGCOR license numbers follow specific formats. Knowing these formats helps you identify fabricated credentials immediately.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>License Type</th>
        <th>Format</th>
        <th>Example</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>e-Games</td>
        <td>eGames-YYYY-NNN</td>
        <td>eGames-2023-047</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>PIGO</td>
        <td>PIGO-YYYY-NNN</td>
        <td>PIGO-2025-008</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Any license number that does not follow this format is suspect. Common fabrications include random alphanumeric strings, license numbers attributed to foreign jurisdictions (like Curacao or Malta) presented as though they authorize Philippine operations, or PAGCOR-branded certificates that use incorrect logos or formatting.</p>

  <h3>Method 3: Direct verification with PAGCOR</h3>

  <p>If you have any doubt, contact PAGCOR directly. The licensing division can be reached at <strong>licensing@pagcor.ph</strong>. The Player Protection Office can be reached through the general PAGCOR contact channels. Response times vary, but PAGCOR will confirm or deny the license status of any operator when asked.</p>

  <p>This is the most reliable method, and it is the one you should use for any platform where you intend to deposit significant amounts. A five-minute email can save you from a platform that has no regulatory accountability whatsoever.</p>

